<FONT SIZE="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="bell gothic bold"><b>Presenting a Marvel of our Times</b></FONT><p><p><FONT SIZE="3" COLOR="#ffffff" FACE="arial, helvetica, sans serif">Langton's 17th Annual Auction<br> December 8 -13, 2001 <IMG SRC="http://www.newlangtonarts.org/images/luminoussmall" WIDTH="212" HEIGHT="153" BORDER="0" ALIGN="right"><br>Prepare to be amazed when Langton reveals the <FONT SIZE="4" COLOR="#ffffff" FACE="bell gothic black">Luminous Wonders of the Electric World!</FONT> </p><p><FONT SIZE="3" COLOR="#ffffff" FACE="arial, helvetica, sans serif"> Let Langton and its generous community of artists and galleries light your way this December. Langton's 17th Annual Auction celebrates the age of invention and illumination, benefiting Langton's artists and programs. Luminous Wonders opens on December 8 and continues with a complimentary champagne tour and silent auction bidding on December 10. The closing night gala kicks off with a catered preview reception and culminates with the closing of live and silent auctions on December 13. <p> This year's contributing artists include Daniel Clowes, Bruce Conner, Chris Finley, Anna Gaskell, Damien Hirst, Jenny Holzer, David Levinthal, Richard Misrach, Deborah Oropallo, Thomas Plagemann, Kathryn Spence, Stephanie Syjuco, Lawrence Weiner, and Robert Wilson, among many others. </p><p>Langton's offerings glow even brighter this year with the inclusion of unique travel packages in our live auction. Travel to New York for an art-infused weekend with dinner at Man Ray and luxurious lodging at the W Hotel in Union Square or relax in Calistoga at Dr. Wilkinson's Hot Spring Resort. Additional packages include a San Francisco "get-away" with theater tickets, dinner, and lodging at Hotel Triton. </p> <p>For tickets and information call 415 626 5416. Advance reservations recommended. <br> A complete schedule of events can be found  <A HREF="http://www.newlangtonarts.org/auction/schej.html" TARGET="body">here</A>.</p><p><FONT SIZE="3" COLOR="#ffffff" FACE="arial, helvetica, sans serif">Thanks to all the high voltage supplied by our <A HREF="http://www.newlangtonarts.org/auction/arlist.html" NAME="arlist" TARGET="body">participating artists</FONT></A> and <A HREF="http://www.newlangtonarts.org/auction/sponsors.html" NAME="sponsors" TARGET="body">sponsors</FONT></A><FONT SIZE="3" COLOR="#ffffff" FACE="arial, helvetica, sans serif"> including <A HREF="http://www.bananarepublic.com" TARGET="blank"><IMG SRC="images/br01logo.jpg"  WIDTH="144" HEIGHT="11" ALIGN="middle"></A>.</font></p>    <p>&nbsp;</p><P><FONT SIZE="3" FACE="arial, helvetica, sans serif"><b><FONT SIZE="4" COLOR="#ffffff" FACE="arial, helvetica, sans serif"><A HREF="http://www.newlangtonarts.org/gal/PNF02" TARGET="body">2002 Potrero Nuevo Fund Prize Applications now available.</A> </FONT></b></p><p><FONT SIZE="3" FACE="arial, helvetica, sans serif">The application is available at New Langton Arts or <A HREF="http://www.newlangtonarts.org/PNF02.pdf" TARGET="blank">online here</A>. Up to four $12,500 awards for artist's projects on urban and social environmentalism. Before you download, make sure you have Acrobat Reader - which you can get for free at <A HREF="http://www.adobe.com/products/acrobat/readstep.html" TARGET="blank">adobe.com</A>. </p><p>  Deadline is November 16, 2001.  Any questions please call Langton at 415 626 5416. There will be three free workshops about the application process and the Prize - click <A HREF="http://www.newlangtonarts.org/gal/PNF02" NAME="PNF02" TARGET="body">here </A>for more info.</font></p><p>The Potrero Nuevo Fund is administered by the Tides Foundation and supports Bay Area community based arts and environmental organizations. Favor goes to art projects that increase accessibility to the making and viewing of art for those traditionally excluded from these experiences.  </font></p> -->